HEADWORD: Aurous
<hw>Au"rous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Containing gold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or derived from,
gold; -- said of those compounds of gold in which this element has its
lower valence; <as>as, <ex>aurous</ex> oxide</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aurum</ent>⟦br⟧
